          <div id="mainInfo" class="hide">
              <div class="container">
                  <div class="row">
                      <div class="col-lg-12">
                        <h1>Corpus Exploration</h1>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <p>
                      In this experiment, you will be asked to explore a corpus of documents and write a summary about it.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                      You will first explore the corpus using an interface that we have designed. 
                      You can think of this interface as a kind of search engine. 
                      But instead of typing in your own queries, 
                      you select from pre-specified “topics” as recommended queries. 
                      By sequentially selecting from these topics, you can zoom in on different parts of the corpus, 
                      eventually reaching a single document. 
                      Instructions on how to use the interface can be found by hovering over the info icon 
                      on the top right of the interface.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                      After the exploration phase, you will be asked to write a summary. 
                      The quality of your summary will be assessed in real-time.
                      When the quality passes a certain threshold, you will be able to submit the HIT. 
                      Therefore, please try to get a good sense of the corpus during the exploration phase.
                  </p>
                  <div>
                      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-md" id="stExp">
                          Start the Experiment.
                      </a>
                  </div>
             </div>
              <div class="footer navbar-fixed-bottom">
