                  <div class="document">
                			<div id="docform" class="form-inline">
                			    <h4>Document</h4>
                          <input type="text" id="docno" style="height: 2.5vw" class="form-control" placeholder="Document Number">
                          <button id="display" class="btn" style="height: 2.5vw; padding:0.5vh";>Display</button>
                      </div>
                      <div id="vd">
                      </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="information" class="hide">
                      <p>This is an interface for you to explore a news corpus with 500 documents. 
                      The corpus is partitioned into topics.
                      You can access individual documents by selecting topics in rounds in the <b>Topics of Current Round</b> panel and 
                      see a record of it in the <b>Topics Selected</b> panel. 
                      At each round, you can also query documents in the <b>Document</b> panel.
                      The goal of this interface is to help you explore and be familiarize with the content of the corpus without 
                      needing to read through too many documents. 
                      You may proceed to the next phase after meeting certain criteria
                      (hover over the <b>status</b> icon to see your status and the criteria).
                      After this exploration phase, you will be asked to write a summary of the corpus.
                      </p>
                      <h5>Topics Selected:</h5>
                        <p>This panel shows the topics that you have selected on each round.
                        Different choices in different rounds will lead you to different documents. 
                        You can see all the topics for a round by hovering over the block for that round. 
                        You can also click on a previous round to go back to that round.
                        </p>
                      <h5>Topics of Current Round:</h5>
                        <p>Select a topic by clicking on a block. 
                        The block shows the top 5 words representing each topic.</p>
                      <h5>Document:</h5>
                        <p>The panel allows you to query a document by entering a number and clicking “Display.” 
                        The number you enter must be within the range shown after "Document Status." 
                        You will see that this range decreases as the number of rounds increases,
                        indicating that you are zooming in on the corpus.
                        </p>
                  </div>
